{"video_id": "35YuILUlfGs", "url": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=35YuILUlfGs", "title": "35YuILUlfGs", "category": "Unknown Category", "fps": null, "segments": [{"start": 0.74, "end": 6.98, "text": "Let's face it, we've all been at one point where an electronic circuit works so well on perfboards"}, {"start": 7.24, "end": 9.36, "text": "that you want to build more units of it."}, {"start": 9.76, "end": 13.5, "text": "But creating these solder traces takes up way too much time."}, {"start": 14.18, "end": 19.44, "text": "Or you ogled a new awesome IC that would be perfect for your next project."}, {"start": 19.72, "end": 26.48, "text": "But sadly it does only exist as an SMD package, which makes perfboard soldering pretty hard to do."}, {"start": 26.48, "end": 39.0, "text": "In both cases creating a proper PCB design and ordering it from a PCB manufacturing house is the way to go to save time and play around easily with SMD components."}, {"start": 39.88, "end": 46.82, "text": "So in this video I will be showing you step by step what to look out for when creating the schematic of your project"}, {"start": 46.82, "end": 55.42, "text": "and how we can then turn it easily into a PCB design that we can order through a couple of simple clicks for quite a low price."}, {"start": 55.42, "end": 57.42, "text": "Let's get started!"}, {"start": 69.42, "end": 77.64, "text": "As a practical example for this video I will be using this relatively simple double-sided PCB that I designed."}, {"start": 78.14, "end": 80.64, "text": "Which brings me to the first step of this tutorial."}, {"start": 81.86, "end": 83.94, "text": "Planning the function of the circuits."}, {"start": 83.94, "end": 88.62, "text": "I knew that I wanted to create a microcontroller based circuit."}, {"start": 88.62, "end": 95.22, "text": "That reads the position of a joystick and then sends the values through the RF band to receiver."}, {"start": 95.94, "end": 99.78, "text": "Also I wanted to power the circuit through a LiPo battery."}, {"start": 99.78, "end": 107.34, "text": "Which means I needed a LiPo charge controller IC, a micro USB port to deliver the power for charging."}, {"start": 107.34, "end": 112.3, "text": "And a power switch to connect the battery voltage to a 3.3V regulator."}, {"start": 112.3, "end": 118.46000000000001, "text": "Which converts the unregulated battery voltage into a suitable voltage for the microcontroller."}, {"start": 118.46, "end": 125.46, "text": "Last but not least I wanted to monitor the battery voltage through a voltage divider with the microcontroller."}, {"start": 125.46, "end": 135.14, "text": "So that when the battery voltage gets close to 3.4V the RF functionality shuts down and the yellow LED lights up."}, {"start": 135.14, "end": 139.82, "text": "And with the function of the circuit planned out it was time for step 2."}, {"start": 139.82, "end": 145.32, "text": "Which involves searching for suitable components and creating a paper schematic."}, {"start": 145.32, "end": 150.0, "text": "For component sourcing I like to use LCSC."}, {"start": 150.0, "end": 152.0, "text": "Because their selection is not only big."}, {"start": 152.0, "end": 157.32, "text": "But also because we will be ordering the PCBs through JLCPCB later on."}, {"start": 157.32, "end": 163.0, "text": "And we can combine that with the LCSC order and thus save shipping costs."}, {"start": 163.0, "end": 167.68, "text": "But anyway once I decided on the main ICs."}, {"start": 167.68, "end": 170.68, "text": "Which were the ATMEGA328 as a microcontroller."}, {"start": 170.68, "end": 174.24, "text": "An NRF24 as the RF transmitter."}, {"start": 174.24, "end": 178.12, "text": "A TP4056 as the charge controller."}, {"start": 178.12, "end": 183.96, "text": "And a TPS76933dBVR as the voltage regulator."}, {"start": 183.96, "end": 186.8, "text": "It was time to think about the packages."}, {"start": 186.8, "end": 191.8, "text": "The package basically describes how the IC will physically look like."}, {"start": 191.8, "end": 197.4, "text": "And determines whether it is a THT or SMD component."}, {"start": 197.4, "end": 203.96, "text": "For example while the NRF24 is only available as a breakout board in THT."}, {"start": 203.96, "end": 208.9, "text": "And the TP4056 is only available as an SMD version."}, {"start": 208.9, "end": 214.28, "text": "We do have the choice between THT and SMD for the microcontroller."}, {"start": 214.28, "end": 217.3, "text": "But since I wanted the circuit to be as small as possible."}, {"start": 217.3, "end": 219.8, "text": "I went with the SMD version."}, {"start": 219.8, "end": 225.4, "text": "Which I also set as the standard for the remaining complementary components."}, {"start": 225.4, "end": 227.4, "text": "Next I planned out on a piece of paper."}, {"start": 227.4, "end": 231.08, "text": "How to connect the main ICs to one another."}, {"start": 231.08, "end": 235.98000000000002, "text": "And also what passive components are necessary to make them all work."}, {"start": 235.98000000000002, "end": 236.78, "text": "To find that out."}, {"start": 236.78, "end": 240.46, "text": "I had a closer look at all the data sheets of the ICs."}, {"start": 240.46, "end": 243.12, "text": "And the recommended example circuits."}, {"start": 243.12, "end": 246.06, "text": "And if everything fails you can always google your question."}, {"start": 246.06, "end": 251.34, "text": "Which should give you a suitable answer in 99% of the cases."}, {"start": 251.34, "end": 255.94, "text": "The last thing to do for the paper circuits was to add breakout points."}, {"start": 255.94, "end": 258.94, "text": "So that I could later program the microcontroller."}, {"start": 258.94, "end": 262.54, "text": "And also hook up the battery and LEDs to the circuits."}, {"start": 262.54, "end": 264.54, "text": "Which will be mounted in a separate enclosure."}, {"start": 264.54, "end": 268.21999999999997, "text": "Now for the passive component selection."}, {"start": 268.21999999999997, "end": 272.22, "text": "I mainly went with 0603 as the package size."}, {"start": 272.22, "end": 276.54, "text": "Which stands for 0.06 by 0.03 inches."}, {"start": 276.54, "end": 280.54, "text": "Or 1.6 by 0.8 millimeters."}, {"start": 280.54, "end": 285.82, "text": "There also exists a 0402 and a 0201 package."}, {"start": 285.82, "end": 290.14000000000004, "text": "But I think 0603 is neither too big or too small."}, {"start": 290.14000000000004, "end": 294.54, "text": "And can still be soldered with an iron with a bit of practice."}, {"start": 294.54, "end": 298.38, "text": "And with the component selection and paper schematic being completed."}, {"start": 298.38, "end": 300.54, "text": "It was time for step 3."}, {"start": 300.54, "end": 303.02000000000004, "text": "Creating a proper schematic."}, {"start": 303.02000000000004, "end": 307.98, "text": "For that I used the EasyEDA free online circuit creator."}, {"start": 307.98, "end": 310.86, "text": "After logging in I created a new project."}, {"start": 310.86, "end": 313.34000000000003, "text": "And there a new schematic."}, {"start": 313.34000000000003, "end": 315.82, "text": "Then I simply used their online library."}, {"start": 315.82, "end": 319.66, "text": "Which also includes pretty much all LCSC components."}, {"start": 319.66, "end": 322.3, "text": "To search for my utilized components."}, {"start": 322.3, "end": 324.86, "text": "And firstly imported them into the workspace."}, {"start": 325.74, "end": 328.14000000000004, "text": "But make sure that you choose components."}, {"start": 328.14000000000004, "end": 330.38, "text": "With the right package and correct footprint."}, {"start": 331.1, "end": 334.54, "text": "Otherwise the PCB design will later not work out."}, {"start": 334.54, "end": 339.42, "text": "Once all the main actors of the circuit were imported."}, {"start": 339.42, "end": 343.34000000000003, "text": "I then used the left aligned resistors with the right package."}, {"start": 343.34000000000003, "end": 345.66, "text": "And capacitors with the right package."}, {"start": 345.66, "end": 347.82000000000005, "text": "As the complementary passive components."}, {"start": 348.86, "end": 350.62, "text": "And of course we should not forget."}, {"start": 350.62, "end": 352.38, "text": "To add male header connectors."}, {"start": 352.38, "end": 353.5, "text": "For the breakout points."}, {"start": 354.70000000000005, "end": 357.18, "text": "Now that we got all of our required components."}, {"start": 357.18, "end": 357.98, "text": "In the editor."}, {"start": 358.62, "end": 361.18, "text": "We can arrange them to logical blocks."}, {"start": 361.18, "end": 363.58, "text": "Which in my case is the power parts."}, {"start": 363.58, "end": 365.1, "text": "And the microcontroller parts."}, {"start": 366.3, "end": 367.42, "text": "Once that was done."}, {"start": 367.42, "end": 370.22, "text": "I utilized the wire function of the software."}, {"start": 370.22, "end": 373.02, "text": "To connect all the components to one another."}, {"start": 373.02, "end": 375.42, "text": "According to how I planned it out on paper."}, {"start": 376.54, "end": 377.58, "text": "Last but not least."}, {"start": 377.58, "end": 379.34000000000003, "text": "I then added the ground."}, {"start": 379.34000000000003, "end": 380.38, "text": "VCC."}, {"start": 380.38, "end": 383.34000000000003, "text": "And battery voltage supply flags to the schematic."}, {"start": 383.34000000000003, "end": 385.18, "text": "Which not only completes it."}, {"start": 385.18, "end": 388.06, "text": "But also ends the third step of this tutorial."}, {"start": 388.06, "end": 391.58, "text": "That means it is time for the last step."}, {"start": 391.58, "end": 392.62, "text": "Step 4."}, {"start": 392.62, "end": 394.78000000000003, "text": "Which is PCB design and ordering."}, {"start": 395.74, "end": 396.46, "text": "For that."}, {"start": 396.46, "end": 399.42, "text": "We firstly have to click the convert to PCB button."}, {"start": 399.98, "end": 402.94, "text": "Which automatically throws all the component footprints."}, {"start": 402.94, "end": 404.38, "text": "Into the PCB editor."}, {"start": 404.94, "end": 407.1, "text": "Shows how to connect them through the blue lines."}, {"start": 407.66, "end": 409.98, "text": "And creates a PCB outline for us."}, {"start": 411.18, "end": 412.62, "text": "The first thing I did though."}, {"start": 412.62, "end": 414.54, "text": "Was removing the outline."}, {"start": 414.54, "end": 416.54, "text": "Because as I mentioned earlier."}, {"start": 416.54, "end": 418.70000000000005, "text": "I needed a specific PCB size."}, {"start": 418.70000000000005, "end": 419.58000000000004, "text": "For the enclosure."}, {"start": 420.54, "end": 421.42, "text": "To do that."}, {"start": 421.42, "end": 423.74, "text": "I changed the measuring system to millimeters."}, {"start": 424.3, "end": 426.70000000000005, "text": "Selected the board outline layer."}, {"start": 426.70000000000005, "end": 427.98, "text": "And used the track tool."}, {"start": 427.98, "end": 430.38, "text": "In combination with the given coordinates."}, {"start": 430.38, "end": 431.98, "text": "In the down right corner."}, {"start": 431.98, "end": 434.14000000000004, "text": "To create the correct size for the PCB."}, {"start": 435.42, "end": 437.74, "text": "Then I moved the micro USB port."}, {"start": 437.74, "end": 439.02000000000004, "text": "The main power switch."}, {"start": 439.02000000000004, "end": 439.90000000000003, "text": "And the joystick."}, {"start": 439.90000000000003, "end": 441.58000000000004, "text": "To the required position."}, {"start": 441.58, "end": 443.5, "text": "According to the enclosure's cutouts."}, {"start": 444.7, "end": 446.3, "text": "To later mount the PCB."}, {"start": 446.3, "end": 448.38, "text": "I also added three pads."}, {"start": 448.38, "end": 449.9, "text": "Whose size I enlarged."}, {"start": 449.9, "end": 452.21999999999997, "text": "So that M3 screws would fit through them."}, {"start": 453.34, "end": 454.62, "text": "And with that being done."}, {"start": 454.62, "end": 457.34, "text": "I placed the rest of the components onto the PCB."}, {"start": 458.38, "end": 459.09999999999997, "text": "Of course."}, {"start": 459.09999999999997, "end": 461.18, "text": "You want to separate the power parts."}, {"start": 461.18, "end": 462.62, "text": "And microcontroller part a bit."}, {"start": 463.18, "end": 464.38, "text": "And also make sure."}, {"start": 464.38, "end": 466.7, "text": "That the pins slash components."}, {"start": 466.7, "end": 467.98, "text": "That need to get connected."}, {"start": 467.98, "end": 469.26, "text": "To one another."}, {"start": 469.26, "end": 471.18, "text": "Are physically close to one another."}, {"start": 471.82, "end": 473.42, "text": "So that the copper trace length."}, {"start": 473.42, "end": 475.02, "text": "Can be as short as possible."}, {"start": 476.21999999999997, "end": 477.42, "text": "As soon as you think."}, {"start": 477.42, "end": 479.18, "text": "Your layout looks logical."}, {"start": 479.18, "end": 481.18, "text": "We could use the given auto router."}, {"start": 481.18, "end": 482.62, "text": "To do the wiring for us."}, {"start": 483.26, "end": 485.5, "text": "But as you might already have guessed."}, {"start": 485.5, "end": 487.5, "text": "That is often not the best solution."}, {"start": 488.38, "end": 490.38, "text": "So let's do it manually."}, {"start": 490.38, "end": 492.46, "text": "By selecting the top layer."}, {"start": 492.46, "end": 493.82, "text": "And using the track tool."}, {"start": 493.82, "end": 495.74, "text": "To simply connect all the components."}, {"start": 495.74, "end": 496.62, "text": "To one another."}, {"start": 497.34, "end": 498.86, "text": "But before doing so."}, {"start": 498.86, "end": 500.46, "text": "We have to talk about the width."}, {"start": 500.46, "end": 501.34, "text": "Of the traces."}, {"start": 501.98, "end": 505.42, "text": "Which is usually set to 0.254 millimeters."}, {"start": 506.62, "end": 509.74, "text": "If we use an online trace width calculator."}, {"start": 509.74, "end": 511.9, "text": "And set the ounce value to 1."}, {"start": 511.9, "end": 513.34, "text": "Which is the standard value."}, {"start": 513.34, "end": 514.86, "text": "For JLC PCBs."}, {"start": 515.4200000000001, "end": 516.7800000000001, "text": "Then the trace could handle."}, {"start": 516.7800000000001, "end": 519.02, "text": "Around 0.885 amps."}, {"start": 519.02, "end": 520.62, "text": "Of current on outer layers."}, {"start": 521.1, "end": 522.0600000000001, "text": "Which is enough."}, {"start": 522.5400000000001, "end": 524.0600000000001, "text": "But I always like to work."}, {"start": 524.0600000000001, "end": 526.38, "text": "With a width of 0.3 millimeters."}, {"start": 527.02, "end": 528.0600000000001, "text": "Since that gives me."}, {"start": 528.0600000000001, "end": 529.58, "text": "A maximum of 1 amp."}, {"start": 530.62, "end": 532.22, "text": "And with that out of the way."}, {"start": 532.22, "end": 534.3000000000001, "text": "I created all possible connections."}, {"start": 534.3000000000001, "end": 535.58, "text": "On the top layer."}, {"start": 535.58, "end": 536.5400000000001, "text": "While making sure."}, {"start": 536.5400000000001, "end": 538.7800000000001, "text": "To not use 90 degree bends."}, {"start": 538.7800000000001, "end": 540.62, "text": "Since that is bad practice."}, {"start": 540.62, "end": 542.62, "text": "And everyone in the comment section."}, {"start": 542.62, "end": 543.34, "text": "Will hate you."}, {"start": 544.54, "end": 545.66, "text": "The only problem."}, {"start": 545.66, "end": 547.34, "text": "With this top layer wiring."}, {"start": 547.34, "end": 549.26, "text": "Was that after a short while."}, {"start": 549.26, "end": 551.34, "text": "I was running out of space."}, {"start": 551.34, "end": 553.18, "text": "And not all necessary connections."}, {"start": 553.18, "end": 553.98, "text": "Were made yet."}, {"start": 554.86, "end": 555.98, "text": "But don't worry."}, {"start": 555.98, "end": 558.14, "text": "Since we can switch to the bottom layer."}, {"start": 558.14, "end": 559.58, "text": "And do the rest wiring there."}, {"start": 560.22, "end": 562.0600000000001, "text": "Which would be very simple to do."}, {"start": 562.0600000000001, "end": 563.9, "text": "For THD components."}, {"start": 563.9, "end": 564.94, "text": "Since the solder pads."}, {"start": 564.94, "end": 566.54, "text": "Penetrate through all layers."}, {"start": 567.42, "end": 568.94, "text": "But for SMD components."}, {"start": 568.94, "end": 569.9000000000001, "text": "We have to create."}, {"start": 569.9000000000001, "end": 570.86, "text": "A so called via."}, {"start": 571.9000000000001, "end": 572.94, "text": "It is basically."}, {"start": 572.94, "end": 573.98, "text": "A small tunnel."}, {"start": 573.98, "end": 575.1, "text": "That connects the top."}, {"start": 575.1, "end": 575.98, "text": "And bottom layer."}, {"start": 576.5400000000001, "end": 577.74, "text": "And just like that."}, {"start": 577.74, "end": 579.2600000000001, "text": "We can finish the wiring."}, {"start": 579.2600000000001, "end": 580.7800000000001, "text": "Even for SMD components."}, {"start": 580.7800000000001, "end": 581.74, "text": "On the bottom layer."}, {"start": 582.7800000000001, "end": 583.9000000000001, "text": "Now here is my finished."}, {"start": 583.9000000000001, "end": 585.0200000000001, "text": "PCB design."}, {"start": 585.0200000000001, "end": 586.3800000000001, "text": "To which you would answer."}, {"start": 586.3800000000001, "end": 587.9000000000001, "text": "It is not finished yet."}, {"start": 587.9000000000001, "end": 589.34, "text": "Since all ground connections."}, {"start": 589.34, "end": 590.0600000000001, "text": "Are not made."}, {"start": 591.1800000000001, "end": 591.74, "text": "Well."}, {"start": 591.74, "end": 592.3800000000001, "text": "For those."}, {"start": 592.3800000000001, "end": 593.58, "text": "We can simply select."}, {"start": 593.58, "end": 594.86, "text": "The top layer."}, {"start": 594.86, "end": 596.7, "text": "And use the copper region tool."}, {"start": 596.7, "end": 598.46, "text": "To encircle the whole PCB."}, {"start": 599.5, "end": 600.62, "text": "And just like that."}, {"start": 600.62, "end": 602.7, "text": "The traces got isolated."}, {"start": 602.7, "end": 604.86, "text": "And the rest of the top layer space."}, {"start": 604.86, "end": 607.1800000000001, "text": "Is used as a solid copper ground layer."}, {"start": 608.1400000000001, "end": 608.7, "text": "Of course."}, {"start": 608.7, "end": 609.5, "text": "If you want to."}, {"start": 609.5, "end": 611.2600000000001, "text": "You could also repeat this process."}, {"start": 611.2600000000001, "end": 612.22, "text": "For the bottom layer."}, {"start": 613.34, "end": 614.3000000000001, "text": "At this point."}, {"start": 614.3000000000001, "end": 615.5, "text": "The PCB design."}, {"start": 615.5, "end": 616.62, "text": "Is basically complete."}, {"start": 617.2600000000001, "end": 617.9000000000001, "text": "Which means."}, {"start": 617.9000000000001, "end": 618.7, "text": "We can click."}, {"start": 618.7, "end": 620.1400000000001, "text": "Generate Gerber files."}, {"start": 620.1400000000001, "end": 621.5, "text": "In order to download them."}, {"start": 621.98, "end": 622.3, "text": "Or."}, {"start": 622.3, "end": 623.26, "text": "We can directly."}, {"start": 623.26, "end": 624.7, "text": "Order our finished products."}, {"start": 624.7, "end": 626.22, "text": "From JLC PCB."}, {"start": 626.94, "end": 627.58, "text": "Which I did."}, {"start": 628.62, "end": 630.22, "text": "And after waiting for a week."}, {"start": 630.22, "end": 631.18, "text": "I was greeted."}, {"start": 631.18, "end": 632.22, "text": "With 10 copies."}, {"start": 632.22, "end": 632.86, "text": "Of my board."}, {"start": 633.42, "end": 635.18, "text": "Which did not only look promising."}, {"start": 635.18, "end": 636.7, "text": "Under the microscope."}, {"start": 636.7, "end": 637.66, "text": "But also worked."}, {"start": 637.66, "end": 638.86, "text": "Without any problems."}, {"start": 639.9, "end": 640.14, "text": "Now."}, {"start": 640.14, "end": 641.1, "text": "If you're curious."}, {"start": 641.1, "end": 642.46, "text": "How to solder the components."}, {"start": 642.46, "end": 643.98, "text": "To such a PCB."}, {"start": 643.98, "end": 644.78, "text": "Then definitely."}, {"start": 644.78, "end": 645.26, "text": "Make sure."}, {"start": 645.26, "end": 646.9399999999999, "text": "To watch my soldering tutorial."}, {"start": 646.9399999999999, "end": 647.98, "text": "About the subjects."}, {"start": 649.02, "end": 649.8199999999999, "text": "As always."}, {"start": 649.8199999999999, "end": 650.86, "text": "I hope you enjoyed."}, {"start": 650.86, "end": 652.22, "text": "Watching this video."}, {"start": 652.22, "end": 653.66, "text": "And learned a thing or two."}, {"start": 653.66, "end": 654.9399999999999, "text": "About PCB design."}, {"start": 655.9, "end": 656.54, "text": "If so."}, {"start": 656.54, "end": 657.9, "text": "Don't forget to like."}, {"start": 657.9, "end": 658.3, "text": "Share."}, {"start": 658.3, "end": 659.02, "text": "And subscribe."}, {"start": 659.9, "end": 661.5, "text": "Stay creative."}, {"start": 661.5, "end": 662.9399999999999, "text": "And I will see you."}, {"start": 662.9399999999999, "end": 664.06, "text": "Next time."}]}